  <title translate="true">Water Supply: Importing Spatial Data</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Water Supply: Importing Spatial Data</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">An AutoCAD Drawing Exchange File (DXF) of the model area named watsup.dxf is distributed with ModelMuse (in the &quot;</text><text styleclass="Figure Referrer" translate="true">My Documents\ModelMuse Examples\</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">data\Water Supply&quot; folder). The first step will be to import this file. &#160;Select </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">File|Import|DXF File...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> &#160;Select watsup.dxf and click the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Open</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button. In the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Import_DXF_File_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Import DXF File</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box, check </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Set values of enclosed cells</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and click the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">OK</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button. Click somewhere on the top view of the model to deselect the imported objects and then click on the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Zoom</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button </text><image src="Zoom.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Zoom button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. &#160;Click and drag on the top view of the model around the imported objects to zoom in on them. The final appearance should be similar to figure 122. In the lower right is the scale for the illustration. &#160;Zoom in on the scale (circle in red in the illustration). &#160;The scale indicates the units of the illustration are feet so change the model units to feet by first selecting </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Model|MODFLOW Options...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> &#160;Then go to the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Options</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab and change the length unit there. &#160;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true">&#32;</text><image src="WaterSupplyStudyArea.ipp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">See caption</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Number" translate="true">Figure 122.</text><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true"> Model after importing DXF file. Scale is circled in red.</text></para>
